  carbohydrates: 32 g
  protein: 72 g
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/rosemary-roasted-butternut-squash-and-butter-bean-cassoulet-54cf95b06ced6e52188b4569
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: American
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees and peel the @butternut squash{3}. Cut the
squash through the middle (widthways) to separate the bulbous bottom from the
top. Cut the bulbous part in half lengthways to expose the seeds. Remove the
seeds with a #spoon{}.

Chop the squash into roughly 2cm chunks and coat in @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} and a
good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Remove the leaves off the
@rosemary{1}(leaves removed and chopped finely), chop finely and scatter on the
squash. Cook on the top shelf of the oven for ~{25%minutes}, or until they're
crispy.

Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the @onion{1/2}(finely diced) and the
@garlic{2%cloves}(finely diced). Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1}. Heat
@olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on low heat. Once hot, add in the onion
and the garlic with a pinch of salt and pepper.

After ~{5%minutes} turn the heat up to medium. Add the butter beans,
@cherry tomatoes{1} and @Italian style herbs{1} and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add
@sugar{1/2%tsp}(if you have some) and season with salt and pepper.

Add @vegetable stock pot{1/2} to the butter beans with @water{150%ml}. Stir
until the stock dissolves. Let the mixture bubble away until it thickens
(about ~{15%minutes}). Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your
@broccoli{2}.

Spread the @almonds{2} on a #baking tray{} then put in the oven for
~{2%minutes} to toast.

> Watch your nuts carefully as they can burn easily.

Once they are done turn the oven off and put the grill on high heat.

Put the broccoli in the boiling water for ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain the broccoli and
keep to the side.

> The broccoli should still have some crunch left in it once cooked.

Toss in @extra virgin olive oil{1%tsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Stir the butternut squash into the stew then put in an #ovenproof dish{}. Scatter
over the @panko breadcrumbs{0.3} and the @hard Italian style cheese{3}(grated)
then grill until golden on top. Serve with the broccoli on the side and a
scattering of the toasted almonds.